&lt;&lt;Is the solution for us to be in every Somalia in the capacity of &quot;meals on wheels&quot; . . .Should we send young American men and women to die in the Rwandas??. . .&gt;&gt;<br><br>
 Looking back on the war we fought it sure makes one wonder about today.  One difference, then we did have a foreign policy--good, bad, we had one.  Now???<br><br>
     Another difference is that we had a Draft---now, with an &quot;All Vol &quot; force, you won't find any sons of professors, lawyers, media, doctors, or congressmen.<br><br>
   It's easy for the Liberals to to send people off on &quot;feel-good&quot; missions  when they know &quot;their sons&quot; won't go.  A &quot;rich man's war, and a poor man's fight.&quot;<br><br>
  The American people should decide if the proper role for the US is to be the worlds policemen and/or nation building.  Are we to right the wrongs everywhere? somewhere?  Defend the weak, feed the hungry, stop tribal murders?  <br><br>
      All the time?  Once in awhile?  Since it's not national interest, what's the criteria for selection? <br><br>
    Keep us very busy, but it's possible, but so very exspensive in resources and people.<br><br>
    Nation building is far from impossible.  Ask the Romans and the Brits as just two examples of &quot;nation building.&quot;  [Napolian gave it a shot as well as &quot;you know who&quot;]  But like war---the principle of Mass applies.  <br><br>
     Can't stick your dxxx in just a &quot;little way.&quot;<br><br>
    It can carry a stigma and sometimes the nataves don't appreciate our stopping thier killing of each other which, lacking TV and the web, they seem to throughly enjoy.   Most enduring tradition most have. <br>
    <br>
    Of course when we do go in, we can often stop them killing each other----they band together [temporarily] to kill us.<br><br>
     Nothing is impossible----if the American people are willing to pay the price in taxes and the lives of their sons and daughters [ lower middleclass only of course].  <br><br>
   I am puzzled however, that during the time when we've done more of this then any other in our history recruitment is down. <br>
 <br>
    Can't understand it as I am certain that those who espouse this are enlisting by the droves and encourging their sons and daughters to enlist to &quot;fight-the good-fight&quot; [pickup the &quot;whiteman's burdan&quot; anyone?].  Look at all the feminists who've enlisted to carry on the fight to get women in the combat jobs---inspiring.  <br><br>
    Be nice to see just one Liberal back up his/her philosophy with their own [or kids] ass---just once.<br>
  <br>
   Just one damn time.<br><br>
